%load_ext autoreload

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%aimport wavenet_features

SR = 16000 # sample rate (Hz)

from IPython.display import Audio, display

def configure_time_axis(ax):
    xticks = ax.get_xticks()
    ax.set_xticks(xticks, xticks / SR * 1e3)
    ax.set_xlabel('Time (ms)')

The dataset¶

All possible pairs of the first three notes in the chromatic scale that starts at A$_3$ (220 Hz)

In [2]:
dataset = wavenet_features.make_chromatic_pairs_dataset(duration_secs=4, sample_rate=SR, n_chromatic_notes=3)

for example in dataset:
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    
    crop_ms = 100
    ax.plot(example[:round(crop_ms * 1e-3 * SR)])
    configure_time_axis(ax)
    plt.show()
    
    display(Audio(example, rate=SR))

Generated examples¶

In [4]:
model = wavenet_features.wavenet_model.load_to_cpu('snapshots/chromatic-pairs-dataset_2022-08-11_16-16-25')
# model = wavenet_features.wavenet_model.load_to_cpu('snapshots/chromatic-dataset_2022-08-1109-04-46')

for example in dataset:
    prefix = example[:model.receptive_field]
    n_generated_samples = 10 * len(prefix)
    
    model.eval()
    generated_example = wavenet_features.generate_example(model, prefix, n_samples=n_generated_samples)
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.plot(generated_example)
    ax.axvline(len(prefix), color='red', linestyle='--')
    configure_time_axis(ax)
    
    plt.show()
